<br>
Thanks for taking the time and care to do a fairly in-depth analysis/updating of the wizard situation. As Sir Yakk noted, the date of the original post was over 10 months ago, when things were far different than what they are today. I've already updated my spreadsheet and formulas to reflect additions which have been added since then:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wiz_dps2/wizdps.htm">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wiz...wizdps.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
... and the excel version:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.zip">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.zip</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Comparing my values at 50% uptime to yours:<br>
I figure 16.35 TDPS, vs your 12.1 TDPS (with the likely source of the difference being my formula accounts for med time (75% of med ticks hit in this case)). When I add KEI and FT1 for a level 50 wiz, I get 20.3 TDPS (vs your 23.6). We are using the same formula to calculate sustainable damage, but I think your meditation calculation rate is off by a bit. From my findings, meditation rate is (med skill)*0.06 + 4, or 19 for a level 50 wiz with max skill (252). This is in addition to innate regen.  Given this, regen should be:<br>
standing: 19.5 mana/tick (3.25 mana/sec)<br>
medding: 38.5 mana/tick (6.42 mana/sec)<br>
Your bottom case, medding 40% of fight time (with 50% of time spent fighting) should yield:<br>
38.5*0.5 + (38.5*0.4 + 19.5*0.6)*0.5 = 38.5*0.7 + 19.5*0.3 = 32.8 mana/tick<br>
This would yield:<br>
(38.5/6) * 8324 / 224 = 20.3 TDPS (50% uptime).<br>
<br>
My current feeling is that wizards with access to focus items, level appropriate buffs, and right click nukes are pretty well balanced against melee in a group environment. This is vastly different than the situation when I began this effort, when FT items were very rare (and didn't stack), before focus items, and Centi weapons were hitting the melee twink market in massive numbers. Wizards should have more access to right click nukes at all levels than is currently the case...<br>
<br>
I was very generous in my equipment allocation for melee (especially at the low-mid levels). It still remains the case that it is far easier to twink a melee than it is a wizard (with the only item that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> really</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> makes a difference being right click nukes -- although mana regen item (and foci) also help.  RBG at 36 is certainly attainable for anyone who already has a character who is 55+ and is starting a melee twink... and if not, FBSS isn't that much worse, performance-wise.<br>
<br>
As for KEI: My goal when setting up the conditions were to use buffs which are level appropriate: meaning I only considered buffs that could be granted by a member of the appropriate class who was the same level or lower. This seemed to be the only fair way to do it, although I will grant that KEI is more easily available now than it was 10 months ago. (10 months ago you couldn't even gate to Nexus and back to Karnors in less than 10 minutes or so).<br>
<br>
Boum covered the issue about factoring healer contribution into tank damage: remember that the wizard needs the tank and the healer to be most efficient in a conventional group, and that additional tanks do not mean additional healing is required. <p>"Evacuate? In our moment of triumph? I think you overestimate their chances!"<BR>
Armok Komra (Triton)<BR>
