Sorcerer Emeritus of Povar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkpaktgrimsoul>Darkpakt Grimsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/19/03 1:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage Logs: Graphing the total damage over time results</span><hr size=1> &quot;However, times have changed. I did update my data just for kicks by giving KEI to wizards at all levels, and it pretty much evens out low level casters and low level twinks.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hmmm I don't know about that.<br>
36 Paladin(mine)<br>
1 hour<br>
OT group<br>
61 kills<br>
<br>
43,262 total melee damage, average of 709 dmg per mob<br>
<br>
That's 135 casts of Ice Shock.  That would cost 21,600 mana.  Without a horse you would lose 472.5 seconds or 78 tics of med time from casting the spell(assuming 3.5 sec focused cast time).  Which would require you to regen mana at a rate of 41 per tic.  With a horse it would be 36 per tic.<br>
<br>
It's a muddy issue though.  If I were to start leveling a wizard from scratch I wouldn't bother buying a horse.  Nobody invites wizards on the assumption that they have KEI, a horse, and full focus.  They invite wizards out of the kindness of their hearts. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
